# Pydantic Schemas

- All schemas inherit from `BaseSchema` (`app.schemas.base`) which sets `model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)`
- Every endpoint must have explicit Pydantic request and response models
- Naming convention: `{Model}Create`, `{Model}Update`, `{Model}Response`, `{Model}InDB`
- Use `Field()` for validation constraints (min_length, max_length, ge, le)
- Use `EmailStr` for email fields (requires `email-validator` package)
- Use `model_dump(exclude_unset=True)` for partial updates
- For paginated responses use `PaginatedResponse[T]` from `app.schemas.base`
